    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Speed&nbsp;</strong> 30 ft., <strong>climb</strong> 30 ft., <strong>fly</strong> 40 ft. (poor)</p>\n<p><strong>Strength&nbsp;</strong> 24 (+7);&nbsp;<strong>Damage&nbsp;</strong> 3d6 S or P;&nbsp;<strong>Size</strong>&nbsp;Large (10-ft. reach)</p>\n<p><strong>Capacity&nbsp;</strong> 20;&nbsp;Usage&nbsp;1/hour</p>\n<p>This biomechanical armor is grown from Swarm remains, assisting its wearer in infiltrating Swarm hives for targeted strikes. A swarm carapace can use its weapon slots to mount both melee and ranged weapons. The wearer gains @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.rX5rK6UWAIOeeipl.JournalEntryPage.p0o9tmWtKZ0qy8DI#telepathy]{Telepathy} that they can use only to communicate with Swarm creatures, can use @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.GMkLZsN3a7YPvA03.JournalEntryPage.aayAhTaRzitONs5U]{Disguise} to take the appearance of a Swarm creature without any DC modifiers for imitating a different creature type, and is treated as a Swarm creature for the purpose of fulfilling other Swarm creatures’ @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.universal-creature-rules.Item.BCdGPzzc8s4vIWFJ]{Swarm Mind} abilities (though the wearer does not gain the benefits of Swarm mind). A shirren wearer reduces the armor’s armor check penalty to –2.</p>\n<p><em>Shirren wearers should toggle the Shirren Armor Check Penalty Reduction modifier on in the modifiers tab.</em></p>"
    },
